Improving indexing for SEO involves ensuring that search engines can easily discover and crawl your website's pages. Here's a guide along with example code to help you improve indexing:

Create a Sitemap: A sitemap is an XML file that lists all the URLs on your 
website, helping search engines understand its structure and prioritize crawling. 
Here's an example of a sitemap XML code:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<urlset xmlns="http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9">
    <url>
        <loc>https://www.example.com/page1</loc>
        <lastmod>2024-04-15</lastmod>
        <changefreq>weekly</changefreq>
        <priority>0.8</priority>
    </url>
    <url>
        <loc>https://www.example.com/page2</loc>
        <lastmod>2024-04-14</lastmod>
        <changefreq>monthly</changefreq>
        <priority>0.6</priority>
    </url>
    <!-- Add more URLs here -->
</urlset>

Replace https://www.example.com/page1 and https://www.example.com/page2 
with the URLs of your website's pages.
<lastmod> indicates the last modification date of the page.
<changefreq> specifies how frequently the page is likely to change 
(e.g., hourly, daily, weekly, monthly).
<priority> provides a hint to search engines about the relative importance of 
the page within the website.
Submit Your Sitemap to Search Engines: Once you have created your sitemap, 
submit it to search engines like Google and Bing using their respective 
webmaster tools or search console platforms.

Optimize Robots.txt File: The robots.txt file tells search engine crawlers 
which pages or directories they can or cannot crawl on your site. Here's an 
example of a robots.txt file:

User-agent: *
Disallow: /admin/
Disallow: /private/

This example disallows crawlers from accessing the /admin/ and /private/ 
directories on your website.
Internal Linking: Ensure that your website's pages are internally linked to 
each other. Internal linking helps spread link equity throughout your site and 
ensures that all pages are accessible to search engine crawlers. Here's an e
example of internal linking HTML code:

<a href="/page1">Page 1</a>
<a href="/page2">Page 2</a>

Replace /page1 and /page2 with the URLs of your website's pages.
Check for Crawl Errors: Regularly monitor Google Search Console or Bing 
Webmaster Tools for any crawl errors on your website, such as broken links or 
inaccessible pages. Fix any errors to ensure smooth crawling and indexing.
By implementing these steps and ensuring that your website's structure is 
crawlable, you can improve indexing and increase the visibility of your website 
in search engine results.